ACTION:
With power applied and PSU confirmed OK, open the power and lift/flip the control cube. Using a multimeter in continuity/ohms mode with power off, trace the two through‑line conductors from the input pair to the output pair and across the switch. Verify: (1) that one conductor from the input is solidly connected to the corresponding output conductor (the 0 V line) with low resistance, and (2) that the other conductor (the +12 V line) is continuous from input to the switch and from the switch to the output when the switch is ON, and open when the switch is OFF. Record whether there is an open circuit, short, or mis‑wiring in the switch or feed‑through path.
